      "example_id": "ex_9a0c7f6191a9463f",
      "topic": "monocultures",
      "example_text": "In the lush fields surrounding Benares, a farmer named Ramesh decided to plant only one type of crop, wheat, across his entire land, believing it would maximize his yield. However, as the season progressed, he noticed that pests began to thrive, and the soil quality deteriorated, leading to a significant drop in his harvest. This scenario illustrates the challenges of monocultures, where relying on a single crop can create vulnerabilities in agriculture, much like how a machine learning model trained on limited data can struggle to generalize effectively.",
